Useful git commands:

clear screen: clear

configuring git process:
git config --global user.name "your name"
git config --global user.email "your email"
git config --global color.ui "auto"
git config --global core.editor "nano -w" or "atom --wait"

make directory: mkdir "directory name"

change directory: cd "directory name"

initialize repository: git init

display status(suuuuuper useful): git status

add file to directory: git add

add all files to directory: git add *

grab files in staging area & puts it in an identified repository: git commit

commit files with message: git commit -m "enter message"

push local repository to finalize changes: git push

list path: pwd

clone repository: git clone "link"

look at changes: git log

add a tag: git tag -a "version"

tag and add message: git tag -a "version" -m "message"

go up a directory: cd ..

grab files from a repository: git pull

look at what's on repository page: git fetch
